Linux: We need Tiling Desktop Environments
Linux：我們需要 Tiling 桌面環境

August 3, 2024 by Hayden James, in Blog Linux
August 3， 2024 by 海登·詹姆斯（Hayden James）， in 部落格Linux

The Linux ecosystem is renowned for its diversity and flexibility, boasting a wide array of distributions (distros) catering to various user needs. However, while there are around a hundred popular and actively maintained Linux distros to choose from, the number of available desktop environments (DEs) pales in comparison.
Linux 生態系統以其多樣性和靈活性而聞名，擁有滿足各種使用者需求的各種發行版 （distros）。然而，雖然有大約 100 個流行且積極維護的 Linux 發行版可供選擇，但相比之下，可用桌面環境 （DE） 的數量相形見絀。

In this blog post, we will discuss the need for more desktop environments that offer built-in support for tiling window management (or non-traditional window management). DEs like the hybrid desktop environment offered by Regolith Desktop (GNOME-Flashback DE + i3 WM), the Pop Shell extension offered by Pop!_OS, and custom-configured XFCE + i3 are all discussed below.
在這篇博文中，我們將討論對更多桌面環境的需求，這些環境為平鋪視窗管理（或非傳統的視窗管理）提供內置支援。下面將討論 Regolith Desktop 提供的混合桌面環境 （GNOME-Flashback DE + i3 WM）、Pop！_OS 提供的 Pop Shell 擴展以及自定義組態的 XFCE + i3 等 DE。

  • Pop!_OS Shell Tiling Window Management  Pop！_OS Shell 平鋪視窗管理

  • The Potential Benefits of Tiling Desktop Environments  平鋪桌面環境的潛在好處

The Disparity Between Linux Distros and Desktop Environments
Linux 發行版和桌面環境之間的差異


GNOME 3, set up as tiling i3 clone. More screenshots, details, and discussion.
GNOME 3，設置為 tiling i3 克隆。更多螢幕截圖、詳細資訊和討論。

When it comes to Linux distributions, there’s no shortage of options. From user-friendly distros like Ubuntu and Linux Mint to more advanced options like Arch Linux and Gentoo, there’s something for everyone! However, this massive level of choice just doesn’t extend to desktop environments.
對於 Linux 發行版，不乏選擇。從Ubuntu和Linux Mint等使用者友好的發行版到Arch Linux和Gentoo等更高級的選項，每個人都能找到適合自己的東西！但是，這種大規模的選擇並未擴展到桌面環境。

Popular desktop environments such as GNOME, KDE, and XFCE offer a polished and cohesive user experience but often lack the customization and keyboard control many power users desire.
流行的桌面環境（如 GNOME、KDE 和 XFCE）提供了精緻而有凝聚力的用戶體驗，但往往缺乏許多高級使用者所需的自定義和鍵盤控制。

On the other hand, tiling window managers (WMs) like i3, dwm, and Sway provide streamlined, keyboard-centric operation, but they sacrifice the full-featured nature of a desktop environment.
另一方面，i3、dwm 和 Sway 等平鋪視窗管理員 （WM） 提供了簡化的、以鍵盤為中心的作，但它們犧牲了桌面環境的全部功能特性。

What’s missing is a greater variety of desktop environments that seamlessly integrate tiling and other alternative window management solutions, allowing users to enjoy the best of both worlds.
缺少的是更多種類的桌面環境，這些環境可以無縫整合平鋪和其他替代視窗管理解決方案，讓使用者可以享受兩全其美。

Here’s a list of the popular Linux desktop environments that I am aware of:
以下是我所知道的流行的Linux桌面環境的清單：

— KDE Plasma, GNOME, Xfce, Lxde, LXQt, MATE, Cinnamon, Pantheon, Deepin, Budgie and Enlightenment.
— KDE Plasma、GNOME、Xfce、Lxde、LXQt、MATE、Cinnamon、Pantheon、Deepin、Budgie 和 Enlightenment。

Here’s a list of the popular tiling stand-alone window managers that I am aware of:
以下是我所知道的流行的平鋪獨立視窗管理員的清單：

— Awesome, Bspwm, dwm, EXWM, Herbstluftwm, i3, NotionWM, Qtile, spectrwm, StumpWM, Sway, wmii, Hyprland, River and xmonad.
— 太棒了、Bspwm、dwm、EXWM、Herbstluftwm、i3、NotionWM、Qtile、spectrwm、StumpWM、Sway、wmii、Hyprland、River 和 xmonad。

We Need More Desktop Environments
我們需要更多的桌面環境


GNOME 44 as a tiling desktop environment. More screenshots, details, and discussion.
GNOME 44 作為平鋪桌面環境。更多螢幕截圖、詳細資訊和討論。

A colleague of mine made a joke in our chat recently while discussing the available options we have of DEs and WMs. When commenting about the current official options available, he said: “Yeah, can’t have your cake and eat it”.
我的一位同事最近在我們的聊天中開了一個玩笑，當時他正在討論 DE 和 WM 的可用選項。在評論目前可用的官方選項時，他說：“是的，不能吃你的蛋糕”。

On his side, he was explaining his interest in attempting to use GNOME 3 and replacing the built-in WM with i3 or Qtile. While on my end, I just finished setting up a less complex GNOME 3, with extensions such as Space Bar and Pop Shell to accomplish an i3-like clone. (above screenshots)
在他這邊，他解釋了他對嘗試使用 GNOME 3 並用 i3 或 Qtile 替換內置 WM 的興趣。在我這邊，我剛剛完成了一個不太複雜的 GNOME 3 的設置，其中包含 Space Bar 和 Pop Shell 等擴展來完成類似 i3 的克隆。（以上截圖）

Incorporating tiling window management directly into the desktop environment enables Linux users to efficiently manage their workspaces and applications without sacrificing the cohesive experience provided by a full-featured desktop environment.
將平鋪視窗管理直接整合到桌面環境中，使 Linux 用戶能夠有效地管理其工作區和應用程式，而不會犧牲功能齊全的桌面環境提供的凝聚力體驗。

Incorporating Tiling WMs into Existing DEs
將平鋪 WM 合併到現有 DE 中


GNOME 44 + Mutter custom Tiling Desktop Environment.
GNOME 44 + Mutter 自定義平鋪桌面環境。

One way to address the need for more hybrid desktop environments is to integrate tiling window management into existing desktop environments yourself.
滿足更多混合桌面環境需求的一種方法是自行將平鋪視窗管理整合到現有桌面環境中。

A desktop environment like GNOME could be adapted to offer more control over window management and greater keyboard control by using GNOME extensions.
通過使用 GNOME 擴展，可以調整像 GNOME 這樣的桌面環境，以提供對視窗管理的更多控制和更好的鍵盤控制。

By building on existing desktop environment window management platforms, developers can create desktop environments that offer the benefits of tiling window management without sacrificing the cohesive, full-featured experience users have come to expect.
通過在現有的桌面環境視窗管理平臺上構建，開發人員可以創建桌面環境，這些環境提供平鋪視窗管理的好處，而不會犧牲使用者所期望的有凝聚力、功能齊全的體驗。

For example, before switching to my current GNOME setup, I also tested Xfce + i3 with very good success. There are some nice guides on YouTube on how to quickly achieve that setup.
例如，在切換到我當前的 GNOME 設置之前，我還測試了 Xfce + i3 並取得了非常好的成功。YouTube 上有一些關於如何快速實現該設置的不錯指南。

There are a few non-GNOME desktop environments using GNOME’s Mutter for window management, for example, Gala and Budgie desktop.
有一些非 GNOME 桌面環境使用 GNOME 的 Mutter 進行視窗管理，例如 Gala 和 Budgie 桌面。

By building on an existing platform like Mutter, developers can create a new desktop environment that offers the benefits of tiling window management without sacrificing the cohesive, full-featured experience users have come to expect. For example, I found Gala as Tiling Window Manager – Idea #01.
通過在 Mutter 等現有平臺上構建，開發人員可以創建一個新的桌面環境，該環境提供平鋪視窗管理的優勢，而不會犧牲使用者所期望的有凝聚力、功能齊全的體驗。例如，我發現 Gala 作為平鋪視窗管理員 – Idea #01。

There are a lot of solutions and tools to work with, build on, combine, or otherwise make use of (Arch Wiki once again FTW!).
有很多解決方案和工具可以使用、構建、組合或以其他方式使用（Arch Wiki 再次 FTW！

Regolith’s Tiling Desktop Environment
Regolith 的 Tiling 桌面環境


Regolith DE – GNOME-flashback (metacity) + i3. More screenshots.
風化層 DE – GNOME-閃回（元城）+ i3。更多螢幕截圖。

A perfect example of a hybrid desktop environment is the aforementioned Regolith Desktop. The new Regolith desktop environment offers multi-distro support with the i3 tiling window manager, providing a unique experience that appeals to both newcomers and experienced Linux users alike.
混合桌面環境的一個完美示例是前面提到的 Regolith Desktop。新的 Regolith 桌面環境通過 i3 平鋪視窗管理器提供多發行版支援，提供獨特的體驗，吸引新手和經驗豐富的 Linux 使用者。

By blending the ease of use and polish of GNOME with the keyboard-centric efficiency of i3, Regolith offers an appealing alternative to traditional desktop environments.
通過將 GNOME 的易用性和優美性與 i3 以鍵盤為中心的效率相結合，Regolith 為傳統桌面環境提供了一個有吸引力的替代方案。

POP!_OS COSMIC Desktop  POP！_OS COSMIC 桌面

POP!_OS, developed by System76, has taken significant strides in enhancing user experience with its COSMIC desktop environment. COSMIC, which stands for “Computer Operating System Main Interface Components,” is a desktop environment that integrates a tiling window manager directly into its UI.
POP！_OS 由 System76 開發，在增強其 COSMIC 桌面環境的用戶體驗方面取得了重大進展。COSMIC 代表「計算機作系統主介面元件」，是一個桌面環境，可將平鋪視窗管理器直接整合到其UI中。

This makes it one of the few desktop environments that natively supports tiling window management out of the box.
這使它成為為數不多的原生支援開箱即用的平鋪視窗管理的桌面環境之一。

COSMIC’s tiling window manager UI allows users to manage their windows efficiently, utilizing keyboard shortcuts for navigation and control. This integration provides the best of both worlds: the streamlined, keyboard-centric operation of tiling window managers and the cohesive, full-featured experience of a desktop environment.
COSMIC 的平鋪視窗管理員 UI 允許使用者有效地管理他們的視窗，利用鍵盤快捷鍵進行導航和控制。此整合提供了兩全其美的效果：平鋪視窗管理員的簡化、以鍵盤為中心的作，以及桌面環境的緊密結合、功能齊全的體驗。

Key features of COSMIC include:
COSMIC 的主要特點包括：

  • Native Tiling Window Management: COSMIC includes built-in tiling options, allowing windows to be arranged automatically to maximize screen real estate and improve workflow efficiency.
    原生平鋪視窗管理：COSMIC 包括內置的平鋪選項，允許自動排列視窗，以最大限度地利用螢幕空間並提高工作流程效率。
  • Customizable Keyboard Shortcuts: Users can configure keyboard shortcuts to navigate and manage windows quickly, enhancing productivity for power users who prefer keyboard-centric operation.
    可自定義的鍵盤快捷鍵：用戶可以組態鍵盤快捷鍵以快速導航和管理視窗，從而提高喜歡以鍵盤為中心的作的高級使用者的工作效率。
  • Seamless Integration: COSMIC is designed to work seamlessly with the rest of the POP!_OS ecosystem, ensuring a smooth and cohesive user experience without the need for extensive configuration.
    無縫整合：COSMIC 旨在與 POP！_OS 生態系統的其他部分無縫協作，確保流暢和有凝聚力的用戶體驗，而無需進行大量組態。

By incorporating these features, POP!_OS COSMIC addresses the need for more desktop environments that offer built-in support for tiling window management. It provides an excellent example of how existing desktop environments can evolve to meet the diverse needs of the Linux community.
通過整合這些功能，POP！_OS COSMIC 滿足了對更多桌面環境的需求，這些環境為平鋪視窗管理提供內置支援。它提供了一個很好的示例，說明現有桌面環境如何發展以滿足Linux社區的多樣化需求。

Pop!_OS Shell Tiling Window Management
Pop！_OS Shell 平鋪視窗管理

Pop Shell is a keyboard-focused interface for GNOME Shell that streamlines navigation and window management. Its defining feature is the implementation of advanced tiling window management, which has been highly desired within the Pop!_OS community.
Pop Shell 是 GNOME Shell 的一個以鍵盤為中心的介面，可簡化導航和視窗管理。它的決定性特徵是實現高級平鋪視窗管理，這在 Pop！_OS 社區中一直非常需要。


Pop!_OS Shell – https://github.com/pop-os/shell
Pop！_OS Shell – https://github.com/pop-os/shell

With the current lack of tiling desktop environment options, many have turned to i3wm as the preferred alternative. However, the extensibility of GNOME Shell provides a great foundation to bring tiling capabilities to the desktop.
由於目前缺乏平鋪桌面環境選項，許多人已將i3wm作為首選替代方案。但是，GNOME Shell 的可擴充性為將平鋪功能引入桌面提供了很好的基礎。

Pop Shell enhances the user experience of GNOME by incorporating the benefits of tiling window management. By combining the strengths of both i3-like tiling and GNOME, Pop Shell offers a seamless solution for efficient window management.
Pop Shell 透過整合平鋪視窗管理的優勢來增強 GNOME 的用戶體驗。通過結合類似i3的平鋪和 GNOME 的優勢，Pop Shell 為高效的視窗管理提供了無縫解決方案。

We Have Enough Linux Distros! The Linux community needs more tiling desktop environments to better cater to the diverse needs of its users.
我們有足夠多的Linux發行版！Linux 社區需要更多的平鋪桌面環境，以更好地滿足其使用者的不同需求。

By offering more desktop environments with built-in tiling window management support, users can enjoy increased productivity, customization, and efficiency without compromise.
通過提供更多具有內置平鋪視窗管理支援的桌面環境，用戶可以在不妥協的情況下享受更高的生產力、自定義和效率。

The Potential Benefits of Tiling Desktop Environments
平鋪桌面環境的潛在好處

The introduction of more tiling desktop environments could provide numerous benefits for Linux users, including:
引入更多平鋪桌面環境可以為 Linux 用戶帶來許多好處，包括：

  • Improved productivity: Tiling window managers enable users to quickly switch between applications and workspaces, allowing them to work more efficiently.
    提高生產率：平鋪視窗管理員使用戶能夠在應用程式和工作區之間快速切換，從而提高工作效率。
  • Greater customization: By integrating tiling window management into desktop environments, users can enjoy increased control over their workspaces and the ability to customize their desktop experience to better suit their individual preferences and workflow.
    更好的定製：通過將平鋪視窗管理整合到桌面環境中，用戶可以更好地控制其工作區，並能夠自定義其桌面體驗以更好地適應他們的個人偏好和工作流程。
  • Enhanced keyboard control: Many power users prefer keyboard-centric operation, as it allows them to navigate and manage their workspaces without being tied to a mouse. Hybrid other desktop environments that incorporate tiling window management can cater to these users by offering extensive keyboard shortcuts customizability.
    增強的鍵盤控制：許多高級使用者更喜歡以鍵盤為中心的作，因為它允許他們在不被滑鼠束縛的情況下導航和管理他們的工作區。包含平鋪視窗管理的混合其他桌面環境可以通過提供廣泛的鍵盤快捷鍵可定製性來滿足這些使用者的需求。
  • Better use of screen space: Tiling window management often results in more efficient use of screen space, as windows are automatically arranged to maximize the available display area. This can be particularly beneficial for users with limited screen real estate or those who work with multiple applications simultaneously. And in a time-saving manner!
    更好地利用螢幕空間：平鋪視窗管理通常可以更有效地利用螢幕空間，因為視窗會自動排列以最大化可用的顯示區域。這對於螢幕空間有限的用戶或同時使用多個應用程式的使用者尤其有益。而且以節省時間的方式！

Expanding the Linux Ecosystem with More Choices
通過更多選擇擴展 Linux 生態系統

While the Linux community already offers an impressive array of distros for users to choose from, there is a limited number of desktop environments that offer non-traditional (MS Windows-like) window management.
雖然 Linux 社區已經提供了一系列令人印象深刻的發行版供用戶選擇，但提供非傳統（類似 MS Windows）視窗管理的桌面環境數量有限。

Quality Over Quantity!  質量勝於數量！

It’s worth noting that the call for more tiling desktop environments doesn’t necessarily mean the introduction of entirely new entries or launches of desktop environments. Existing desktop environments can also evolve by adding support for tiling window management to their current offerings.
值得注意的是，對更多平鋪桌面環境的呼籲並不一定意味著引入全新的條目或推出桌面環境。現有桌面環境也可以通過向其當前產品加入對平鋪視窗管理的支援來發展。

This approach could make popular desktop environments like GNOME, KDE or XFCE even more attractive to users who desire a tiling window management option without having to switch to a tiling WM.
這種方法可以使 GNOME、KDE 或 XFCE 等流行的桌面環境對那些希望使用平鋪視窗管理選項而不必切換到平鋪 WM 的使用者更具吸引力。

By combining the best aspects of full-featured desktop environments and tiling window managers, these hybrid solutions can provide an optimal experience for a wide range of users.
通過結合功能齊全的桌面環境和平鋪視窗管理器的最佳方面，這些混合解決方案可以為廣泛的使用者提供最佳體驗。

Conclusion  結論

The Linux ecosystem thrives on its diversity and the numerous options it provides to users. However, there’s still room for improvement when it comes to desktop environments.
Linux 生態系統因其多樣性和為使用者提供的眾多選擇而蓬勃發展。但是，在桌面環境方面仍有改進的空間。

By developing more desktop environments that offer built-in support for tiling window management and other non-traditional WM solutions, the Linux community can cater to the needs of a broader range of users and continue to enhance the overall Linux experience without forcing users to choose between DEs or WMs.
通過開發更多為平鋪視窗管理和其他非傳統 WM 解決方案提供內置支援的桌面環境，Linux 社區可以滿足更廣泛使用者的需求，並繼續增強整體 Linux 體驗，而無需強迫使用者在 DE 或 WM 之間進行選擇。

In other words, the emergence of solutions like Regolith Desktop represents a step in the right direction in allowing users to – have their cake and eat it too! – as it were. There are so many possible combinations!
換句話說，像 Regolith Desktop 這樣的解決方案的出現代表了朝著正確方向邁出的一步，讓使用者 - 擁有他們的蛋糕，也吃掉它！- 就像它一樣。有這麼多可能的組合！

By doing this, we can continue to expand the Linux ecosystem to provide users with an even greater array of no-compromise choices to suit individual needs and preferences.
通過這樣做，我們可以繼續擴展 Linux 生態系統，為使用者提供更多不折不扣的選擇，以滿足個人需求和偏好。

    WMs as shipped lack battery management/status, HiDPI support, accessibility features, network management/notifications, VPN support, external storage management, media players, display management (needs manual multi-monitor setup), volume management, screen brightness, night shift, Bluetooth, printing and a bunch of other stuff that has to be set up manually.

    Unless you are on very old hardware there not much reason as say 5 to 10 years ago to using WMs only setups that thrive on low end hardware.

    That said, just like Arch, some people like that manual route.

    But I agree! tiling on desktop envs would be cool as an official option. Checking out Regolith!

  5. Pyro

    I think your points about tiling wms are either misguided, outdated, or only taking one or two into account. I’ll off my rebuttal to each of your points below.

    Wms sure don’t ship with advanced settings support like you mentioned, because like you said you set it up manually, this makes it kinda like a piece together your own de kinda think which I do like, I 2ould like to mention that Wayland based tiling compositors (Wayland’s version of a wm since the compositor and wm are the same thing in Wayland) like sway and hyprland do have monitor settings and hidpi settings natively, just configured in the conf file instead of via gui. That being said there is also wdisplays that allows for de/wm agnostic monitor configuration in a gui.

    I’m currently running hyprland on my gaming desktop and honestly have never been happier. Games don’t minimize when I mouse over to discord, games run smooth as butter and VR setup was a breeze. I’m also running hyprland on my 11th Intel inside dell laptop that I use for work and have no complaints there, I mostly just use autocpu-freq to manage performance vs battery life, it’s a set it and forget it tool with good defaults. So I strongly disagree that tiling wms are best at home on old hardware, you just have to set them up in a way that works for you.

    Did hit the nail on the head though I am an arch user who likes things exactly how I want them, so I’m likely the exception, that being said getting hyprland up and running exactly how I wanted it was pretty easy and straight forward. I’d highly recommend checking it out, you do need to manually assign the media keys like volume and brightness but all in all it’s pretty sick.
